        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 3:50PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 350 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Tails Creek, or 9 miles
southeast of Chatsworth. This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Heavy rain may cause temporary street flooding especially
in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Mountaintown, Carters, Fort Mountain State Park, Tails Creek, and
Ramhurst.
</description>
        <instruction>Motorists should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of
control due to hydroplaning.</instruction>
